# Agno — Game Dev Crew

Separate **Python** project from the game: dependencies in [`pyproject.toml`](pyproject.toml). Do not mix Agno/OpenRouter dependencies into the game repo’s `package.json`.

## Layout (`game_dev_crew/`)

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Config + model | `config.py` (`repo_root`, `load_instruction`, `make_model`) |
| CLI | `cli.py` — `game-dev-crew` command |
| Agents / teams | `crew/agents.py`, `crew/teams.py` |
| AuditFlow + Reviewer parse | `workflow/audit_flow.py`, `workflow/reviewer_parse.py` |
| Scene generation workflow | `workflow/scene_generation_flow.py` |
| Allowlisted tools | `tools/repo_read.py`, `tools/repo_glob.py`, `tools/allowlisted_shell.py`, `tools/validate_scenes.py`, `tools/policy.py` |
| Exportable prompts | `instructions/*.md` — **only** source of text for `Agent(instructions=…)` |

## Conventions

- **Game repo:** `REPO_ROOT` (root with `package.json`). The engine and campaign live in the game repo (e.g. `src/`); the crew only reads/validates via tools.
- **Instructions:** keep **real paths** in `.md` files to reduce hallucination. Scene files and IDs: **English**; player-facing copy: **PT-BR** — applies to *content* the agents discuss, not Python file names.
- **Tool safety:** follow [`tools/policy.py`](game_dev_crew/tools/policy.py) — `glob` + `read_repo_file` are read-only; `execute_command`/`bash` only allowlisted `npm run` (`ENABLE_REPO_SHELL_TOOLS`); `validate:scenes` on **all** agents only with `ENABLE_VALIDATE_SCENES_TOOL`; no file writes by agents through these tools.
- **AuditFlow:** the `- ❌ [owner]` format and `STATUS: APPROVED` in [`instructions/reviewer.md`](game_dev_crew/instructions/reviewer.md) align with `reviewer_parse.py`; changing one side means aligning the other and the loop in `audit_flow.py`.
- **KISS:** minimal, focused changes.

